SIMPLE: unship
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unship
<hw>Un*ship"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>ship</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To take out of a ship or vessel; <as>as, to
<ex>unship</ex> goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To remove or detach, as any part
or implement, from its proper position or connection when in use;
<as>as, to <ex>unship</ex> an oar; to <ex>unship</ex> capstan bars; to
<ex>unship</ex> the tiller</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unshipment</ent>⟦br⟧
